The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 London, March 19 (PTI): A Sikh magistrate of Indian origin has been handed a jail term of 18 months in Britain for telling a businessman friend that he could make a court case against him disappear for 45,000          
	Balbir Singh Sandhu had told the businessman, being prosecuted for employing illegal workers in his factory, that he had access to the case files.                  
	New Delhi (PTI): A court has asked ICICI Bank to pay Rs 50,000 to a customer whose motorcycle it had forcibly repossessed while he was riding it. The Delhi district consumer forum (north) said a financial company could not be allowed to repossess a vehicle forcibly while it was plying on a road.                   
	 Pune (PTI): Pandit Bhimsen Joshi has been admitted to hospital with pneumonia. Hospital sources on Wednesday described the 87-year-old singers condition as stable.                   
	Madikeri (PTI): A man was trampled to death by a wild elephant on Tuesday in this tourist spot in Karnataka. Forest officials have promised compensation to the family of Aravind, 65. Local people accused the forest officials of not using funds allocated for solar fencing to prevent elephants from entering villages.                  
	Chennai (PTI): Actor Raghuvaran, 49, died in a hospital on Wednesday following a brief illness. He had acted in more than 80 Tamil and Malayalam films. He had also starred in Hindi films like Ram Gopal Vermas Shiva and Mani Ratnams Anjali.                                                                                                                           
